                'heading_ms' => 'PENGENALAN JURNAL REFLEKSI',
                'heading_en' => 'REFLECTION JOURNAL INTRODUCTION',
                'text_ms'    => "Penulisan Jurnal Refleksi Latihan Industri adalah salah satu elemen penting dalam penilaian Kursus Latihan Industri. Pelajar dikehendaki mencatat segala aktiviti harian yang dilaksanakan di organisasi latihan. Setiap minggu pelajar perlu menulis refleksi dan mendapatkan pengesahan serta maklum balas daripada Penyelia. Jurnal Refleksi Latihan Industri pelajar ini akan dinilai oleh Pengurus Industri.\n\nDi samping itu, sepanjang menjalani latihan industri ini, saya didedahkan dengan perkara-perkara dan pengalaman yang baru. Selain dari mempraktikkan apa yang telah saya belajar sepanjang lima (5) semester pengajian di Politeknik Sultan Idris Shah, saya juga telah didedahkan bagaimana cara untuk mengikuti setiap arahan dan peraturan-peraturan yang telah ditetapkan sepanjang saya menjalani latihan industri di Opensoft Technologies. Di syarikat ini, saya telah diletakkan di Bahagian Pembangunan Perisian. Tempoh perkhidmatan saya bermula pada hari Isnin sehingga hari Jumaat mengikut waktu bekerja yang ditetapkan iaitu dari jam 8.30 pagi sehingga 5.30 petang. Berikut merupakan ringkasan mingguan sepanjang saya menjalani latihan industri selama 20 minggu (12 Januari 2026 sehingga 29 Mei 2026).",
                'text_en'    => "Writing the Industrial Training Reflection Journal is one of the important elements in the assessment of the Industrial Training Course. Students are required to record all daily activities carried out at the training organisation. Each week, students need to write reflections and obtain verification and feedback from their Supervisor. The student's Industrial Training Reflection Journal will be assessed by the Industry Manager.\n\nIn addition, throughout this industrial training, I was exposed to new things and experiences. Apart from practising what I learned during five (5) semesters of studies at Politeknik Sultan Idris Shah, I was also exposed to how to follow every instruction and regulation set throughout my industrial training at Opensoft Technologies. At this company, I was placed in the Software Development Department. My service period is from Monday to Friday following the working hours set from 8.30 am to 5.30 pm. The following is a weekly summary throughout my 20-week industrial training (12 January 2026 to 29 May 2026).",
